data.title: Pad Troubleshooting for iRobot® Braava jet™ Mopping Robot
data.description: This video shows how to solve pad issues for your iRobot® Braava jet™. To check if there is a problem with your Braava jet™ cleaning pad, turn off the robot by holding down the clean button. Remove the pad, and wipe the underside of the robot with a clean, dry cloth. Now, rotate the pad and reinstall. Restart the robot by pressing the clean button twice.

data.title: Mobility Troubleshooting for iRobot® Braava jet™ Mopping Robot
data.description: This video shows how to solve mobility issues for your iRobot® Braava jet™ Mopping Robot. Turn the robot upside down, and clean the cliff detect sensors on the front and back of the robot with a clean, dry cloth. Tap the bumper a few times to clear any debris. Check the wheels for any obstacles and clear away any hair or debris that has built up. Lastly, check to make sure the Braava jet™ pad has not been damaged. If it has, switch to a new Braava jet™ pad.

data.title: Virtual Wall® Mode for iRobot® Braava jet™ Mopping Robot
data.description: This is an instructional video on using the Virtual Wall® Mode for your iRobot® Braava jet Mopping Robot. To prevent Braava jet™ from going into other rooms, an invisible barrier can be created with Virtual Wall® Mode so that the robot will avoid cleaning part of a room or a different floor type. You can also use Virtual Wall Mode to divide a larger room into smaller areas to help Braava jet clean more efficiently.

data.title: Cleaning Patterns for iRobot® Braava jet™ Mopping Robot
data.description: This is an instructional video on cleaning patterns for your iRobot Braava jet Mopping Robot. Braava jet mops and sweeps kitchens, bathrooms, and other small spaces in an efficient, systematic cleaning pattern. It automatically selects the correct cleaning method based on pad type and tackles dirt and stains on hard floors.

data.title: Selecting a cleaning pad for iRobot® Braava jet™ Mopping Robot
data.description: This is an instructional video for selecting a cleaning pad for your iRobot® Braava jet™ Mopping Robot. Braava jet™ comes with a sample pack of Wet Mopping, Damp Sweeping, and Dry Sweeping cleaning pads. Braava will automatically recognize the pad and adjust its cleaning behavior based on the pad you choose. Choose a cleaning pad that matches how you want to clean your floor.

data.title: Ejecting the Cleaning Pad for iRobot® Braava jet™ Mopping Robot
data.description: This is an instructional video for ejecting the cleaning pad for your iRobot® Braava jet™ Mopping Robot. To eject the Braava jet™ Cleaning Pad without touching the dirt, lift the handle and pull back on the pad eject button. Disposable cleaning pads can be dropped directly into the trash and Washable Cleaning Pads (sold separately) can be dropped into the laundry bin.

data.title: Filter Care for iRobot® Braava jet™ Mopping Robot
data.description: This is an instructional video to care for your filter on your iRobot® Braava jet™ Mopping Robot.  Perform the filter care procedure to keep Braava jet™ running at peak performance. Pull from the rim of the tank to remove the filter. Avoid pulling from the tank cap. Turn the filter upside down and run it under warm tap water. To reinstall, align the filter with the tank opening and push straight down until it clicks into place.
